BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/WhatsApp-Image-2026-02-25-at-18.00.29.jpeg
CATEGORIES:Performances,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260522T114213Z
DESCRIPTION:Long before the language of inclusion entered our workplaces\, India held space for gender in all its complexity through diverse cultural and spiritual traditions. The Jogappas are one such living tradition — a transgender community whose identity\, livelihood\, and spiritual practice have remained deeply intertwined for centuries through devotion to Goddess Yellamma.\n\nSacred Rhythms\, Living Histories of Jogappa community invites audiences into this world through an intimate cultural experience where music\, storytelling\, and handmade instruments carry forward a tradition rooted at the intersection of faith\, folklore\, and identity. Drawing from rich oral histories across north Karnataka\, south Maharashtra\, west Telangana\, and Andhra Pradesh\, the Jogappas perform devotional compositions in praise of Goddess Yellamma while sharing glimpses into their lived realities and cultural heritage.\n\nIn collaboration with the Solidarity Foundation\, this interactive session brings together the lived cultural knowledge of the Jogappa tradition and academic perspectives on its history\, music\, and spiritual practice\, offering audiences a rare opportunity to listen closely\, engage meaningfully\, and deepen their understanding of this powerful living art form.
DTEND:20260606T140000Z
DTSTART:20260606T123000Z
SUMMARY:Sacred Rhythms\, Living Histories of Jogappa community
UID:1293@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/sacred-rhythms-living-histories-of-jogappa-community/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/2-5.png
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260525T140953Z
DESCRIPTION:“A hat is a mood. It’s a feeling\,” says the famed milliner Philip Treacy. Headgear–designed\, sculpted\, pieced together–can be very expressive accessories. Join us for a workshop where we make our own funky headgear and write slam poetry inspired by the Beneath the Turning Sky exhibition. \n\nThis is a workshop for you to explore how costume and voice can come together to aid self-expression in fun\, exciting ways!\n\nThis programme is hosted in conjunction with the Teen Takeover programme.
DTEND:20260606T080000Z
DTSTART:20260606T060000Z
SUMMARY:Wear the Sky
UID:1290@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/wear-the-sky/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Screenshot-2026-05-22-165600.png
CATEGORIES:Film Screenings,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260601T094531Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a weekend of queer short film screenings that bring into focus stories of identity\, resistance\, joy\, and community from across the country. Through intimate and thought-provoking narratives\, these films explore the realities of queer lives\, reflecting on visibility\, belonging\, resilience\, and self-expression in a time marked by increasing invisibilisation and protest.\n\nSpanning diverse experiences and perspectives\, the screenings invite audiences to engage with stories that challenge silence and reclaim space through the power of storytelling. Accompanied by conversations and reflections with speakers and community voices\, the programme creates space for dialogue rooted in solidarity\, and queer joy.\n\nThe film list will be announced shortly.\n\nThis programme is part of LGBTQIA+ programming and is an attempt to amplify narratives from within the queer community through film\, dialogue\, and collective reflection.
DTEND:20260607T113000Z
DTSTART:20260606T093000Z
SUMMARY:Queer Film Evenings
UID:1295@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/queer-film-evenings/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Screenshot-2026-05-22-160624.png
CATEGORIES: Featuring,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260522T113526Z
DESCRIPTION:Being a teenager isn't easy. You're navigating a whole new world\, trying to make sense of it\, figure out what excites you\, what doesn't\, and who you're becoming along the way. As part of our Teen Takeover programme\, we're opening the doors for an after-hours session that's entirely yours! Come together with other teenagers to explore Beneath the Turning Sky\, our permanent exhibition\, before settling in for a peer-led art therapy session. This session will include meditative mandalas\, colouring\, drawing and more creative ways to slow down\, tune in and express yourself.\n\nNo fixed agenda. No pressure. Just space to hang out\, listen to each other and make something together inside the museum.\n\nThis programme is hosted in conjunction with the Teen Takeover programme.
DTEND:20260606T120000Z
DTSTART:20260606T110000Z
SUMMARY:Teens After-Hours
UID:1292@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/teens-after-hours/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/image.jpeg
CATEGORIES:Performances,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260522T114141Z
DESCRIPTION:Blending storytelling\, drag performance\, dance\, and multimedia elements\, the program traces KaMani Sutra’s journey of discovering femininity while navigating life as an adult immigrant in the United States.\n\nRooted in the richness of Indian drag aesthetics and cultural influences\, this artist's showcase reflects on identity\, migration\, and self-expression\, contrasting the freedom of living authentically in a foreign land with the complexities of belonging and visibility. Through short performances\, video\, and consensual audience participation\, the lecture-performance-artist showcase challenges ideas around the model minority myth\, binary gender\, and colonial saviorship.\n\nAt once celebratory and reflective\, the program honours intergenerational queerness\, LGBTQ+ community\, saris\, mujras\, divine femininity\, and the transformative power of self-love.\n\nThis programme is part of LGBTQIA+ programming and is an attempt to amplify narratives from within the queer community through film\, dialogue\, and collective reflection.
DTEND:20260607T140000Z
DTSTART:20260607T123000Z
SUMMARY:Being Queen is My Resistance: Lessons in Drag Mythology and Migration
UID:1294@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/being-queen-is-my-resistance-lessons-in-drag-mythology-and-migration/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/PTG.01769-e1779445722719.webp
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260522T113620Z
DESCRIPTION:Beneath the Turning Sky explores how we find our place in this world. How have our choices shaped what we are left with today\, and what are the weighty myths\, stories and headlines that trace our endless attempts to understand the cosmos?\n\nIn this workshop\, participants will be given a peer-led walkthrough of Beneath the Turning Sky by Job\, one of our Teen Takeover participants\, following which they will be required to research and act out various time periods covered within the exhibition and depict the cycles of wonder\, destruction\, exploitation and creation.  \n\nThrough this exercise\, the hope is to help us understand the vicious cycles that we are stuck in and how to break out of them and imagine more hopeful futures.\n\nThis programme is hosted in conjunction with the Teen Takeover programme.
DTEND:20260606T103000Z
DTSTART:20260606T093000Z
SUMMARY:What the Sky Sees
UID:1291@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/what-the-sky-sees/
END:VEVENT
